programme.desc: For the past 12 years Sue Chamberlain has been harbouring a devastating secret. She's entirely lost her confidence and her youth. Presenter Nicky Hambleton-Jones and a team of experts revive Sue's confidence.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Bringin’ Back the Lovin’ Feeling
programme.desc: As a working mom of two toddlers, Sara has no time for hairstyles and fancy clothes. She used to spend hours in the gym but now she's traded in her workout schedule for changing diapers and story time.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Life Lessons for Linda
programme.desc: Linda's a stay-at-home mom whose two sons have left the nest for college, so she's decided to go back to school as well! Not wanting to be viewed as the "Mom" on campus, Linda wants to update her appearance so she can look and feel more confident.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Truly A Trophy
programme.desc: Rapid aging as a result of early menopause left Deborah feeling stressed out and feeling anything but sexy. She is sick of spending her days in sweats and wants to feel like a woman again.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 10
programme.desc: The family have been squatting at Leopard's Den as they prepare to make their last stand to prevent the bulldozers from destroying their home. Du Plessis and Fatani bring elephants and a giraffe to dissuade the construction crew from moving in.

programme.title: Wild At Heart
programme.desc: After the devastating loss of Leopard's Den, the family are split across continents. Caroline, Liv and a heavily pregnant Alice are in the UK, while Danny and Du Plessis have remained in South Africa.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2
programme.desc: Danny returns to South Africa with Caroline, Liv and Charlotte. They are all excited to be back and are looking forward to seeing their new home, Clearwater Farm.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Danny has been preparing his pitch for an Endangered Species Project. JLW, a pharmaceutical company, are looking to fund an environmental project and the family hope that this grant money will enable them to buy Leopard's Den and Mara.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: Danny and Ed release two cheetah brothers together, a symbol of their new partnership, but not all of the family are happy about this new start. Caroline is still furious at what she sees as Danny's betrayal of Du Plessis.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: The family are still estranged following Caroline's decision to move back to the decrepit Clearwater house with Du Plessis. Rosie is determined to reunite everyone, and plans a civilised dinner as a step towards reconciliation.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6
programme.desc: Danny is in prison, accused of murdering Peeters, but Du Plessis is determined to prove his friend's innocence by any means he can. Du Plessis' first attempt backfires disastrously when he harangues a police officer and ends up in a cell next to Danny.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 7
programme.desc: With Danny away, and Du Plessis undertaking an ignominious stretch of community service, Ed is left in charge of running the Endangered Species Project.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 10
programme.desc: A motocross rider may have broken his back after hitting a tree head on at high speed, at a sawmill a man faces its worse nightmares; and a woman is fighting for her life after taking an accidental overdose of her husband's medication.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: A young man has flipped his quad bike and can't move his neck. Later that night, the crew is called to a suburban house because a DIY homebuilder has fallen through the roof in his house – and there's a bone sticking out through his jeans.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: De Anna and her husband were celebrating their 50th wedding anniversary on board a luxury liner. The ship's doctor radios for help. But the liner is a long way out at sea. Can the rescue crew get to De Anna in time?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: 14 year-old motor-cross rider, Kacee gets the death wobbles and cartwheels over the top of his handle bars and hits the ground head first. He's now struggling to breath and is barely able to talk. Team Air Rescue needs to get Kacee to the hospital fast.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: Fishing buddies Scott, Wayne and Wayne's son Andrew head out to their favorite fishing spot, but when a freak wave hits their boat they have no choice but to SOS for help. Within minutes, the boat capsizes. Can the Air Rescue crew get to them in time?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: 71 year-old retired nurse Sandra was exploring Tasmania's Cradle Mountain when she slipped and fractured her wrist. She's in excruciating pain and night is falling. Visibility is dangerously low. Can the rescue team get in close enough to get them out?

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 1
programme.desc: Auckland's Westpac helicopter crew races to save two teenage girls fighting for their lives after their car crashed and rolled the Waiwera Hill.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 2
programme.desc: Professional scuba diver Brian Green has been found floating and not breathing, and is on a boat near the Noises, a group of islands in the Hauraki Gulf. The team has to move fast.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 3
programme.desc: On Great Mercury Island near Coromandel, a scuba diver has surfaced unconscious without a pulse. Without Rescue 1 he may soon be dead.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 4
programme.desc: The Rescue 1 team respond to a call out where an elderly couple in their 60s are in a critical condition after a head on collision.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 5
programme.desc: A truck driver who had one leg amputated 40 years ago, has crashed his truck and crushed his remaining leg. If Rescue 1 can't get him to hospital in time, he will bleed to death.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: Mountain bike fanatic, Blake was out riding when he clipped a tree and crashed into a rock. It's a time critical rescue mission. And what the rescue crew doesn't yet know is that Blake is about to take a turn for the worse.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: Motorbike rider, Lachlan was testing out his newly designed dirt-bike track when he lost control on a jump. His femur has been badly shattered. The Air Rescue crew is tasked with flying Lachlan to hospital but his medical dramas have only just begun.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: Retirees Diane and husband Gary were just a few hours into their Pacific Island cruise of a lifetime when disaster struck. Diane toppled down a set of stairs and now she's in need of urgent medical attention.

programme.title: Made In: BMW Sustainability
programme.desc: By putting many thoughts into the cutting process of raw materials, BMW reduces the amount of waste drastically. Most of the 600 tons of sheet metal that are produced by BMW’s pressing plant ends up in the final cars, while only 10 kg go to waste.

programme.title: Made In: 125 Years of Mercedes-Benz
programme.desc: Mercedes-Benz celebrates 125 years of automotive history. 1926 the brand name arises as a result of the consolidation of Mercedes, the Daimler Motor Company and Benz by Benz & Co.

programme.title: Made In: Kiekert
programme.desc: Kiekert from North Rhine-Westphalia in Germany is a supplier for many different locking systems and the market leader in side door locks. Customers from all over the world buy door locks from Kiekert.

programme.title: Made In: Audi R8 GT
programme.desc: By now, Audi has sold more than 16,000 sports cars around the world. In 2010 they upped the stakes even more and introduced the Audi R8 GT. The high performance sports car is limited on 333 units.

programme.title: Made In: Alpina
programme.desc: Alpina symbolizes modern engineering, high precision in engine design and finest materials. The green and blue cachet has guaranteed highest quality for more than 40 years. Alpina specializes in premium BMW tuning and successful motorsports.

programme.title: Made In: Self-Driving Cars
programme.desc: Autonomous driving, which means that the car operates independently, sounds like a crazy idea, but is seen as the future of mobility. Steps towards this reality are already done thanks to the progress made in Germany.

programme.title: Made In: BMW Series 5 GT, Part 1
programme.desc: In 2003 the automotive industry was booming like never before and the law of supply and the supply-demand system works perfectly. So many manufacturers decided to develop new cars.

programme.title: Made In: BMW Series 5 GT, Part 2
programme.desc: The automotive industry is a brutal business and the genesis of new models is a jealousy kept secret. However, Made In was able to document the production history of a BMW model.

programme.title: Made In: Volkner Mobile
programme.desc: With its length of up to 12 meters and its weight of 18 tons, the Performance by Volkner is the most extraordinary luxury motor home from Germany and one of the most exclusive carvans in the world.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Adventure bike for globetrotters / Bike Tour through Scotland
programme.desc: The Honda Africa Twin is back. From 1988 to 2004, it was the ultimate bike for enduro fans. The model of the modern era is hunting down the competition from BMW and KTM. We investigate the secret of its success.
programme.sub-title: Adventure bike for globetrotters / Bike Tour through Scotland

programme.title: Motorcycles: BMW
programme.desc: An incredible 215 hp with a total weight of only 149 kilos: the BMW HP4 RACE is a true racing bike. The model is limited and highly sought-after.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Carbon-Bikes / Ducati
programme.desc: Carbon has been used in racing for decades. But it's new that the lightweight yet very strong material is finding favour in motorbike construction. And it is this kind of lightweight construction that racing driver Julius Ilmberger specialises in.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Harley-Davidson
programme.desc: Dyna Switchback, Sportster 72 and Softail Slim were the names of the Harley newcomers on show in the showrooms. They appealed to completely different target groups, which each of the three motorbikes managed to do in its own unique way.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Honda / KTM / Suzuki
programme.desc: The 1970s are back. For years, motorbike nostalgia has been spreading all over the world. Honda once produced the first ever four-cylinder bike, the CB 750 Four. Now the Japanese are invoking their own tradition with the CB 1100 EX.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Room & Board
programme.desc: The owners of a vacation lodge in the remote town of North Hudson, NY, feel their woodsy getaway is plagued by negative spirits.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Lady Vampire
programme.desc: PRS investigates a case involving single mom, Dawn, and her 5-year-old daughter, both of whom are tormented by the appearance of a hag they call "lady vampire."

programme.title: Paranormal State: Return of the Dead: Glove II
programme.desc: PRS returns to the site of one of their most famous cases, Daisytown, PA, where they had discovered a glove print of an old miner that they determined was the spirit of a Great-Grandfather.
programme.sub-title: Return of the Dead: Glove II

programme.title: Paranormal State: Haunted Homecoming
programme.desc: Ryan brings PRS to his hometown of Sumter, SC to investigate a chilling case where a young boy was tragically shot and killed on a front doorstep while trick-or-treating on Halloween.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Mothman
programme.desc: Ryan takes his team to Point Pleasant, West Virginia to investigate his own personal holy grail of paranormal lore: the mysterious Mothman.

programme.title: Paranormal State: First Contact
programme.desc: Washington State, a hotbed of unexplained paranormal activity. Between possible UFOs in the sky and winged creatures in the woods, Ryan and his team are forced to face their fears and deal with the question: Are we truly alone in the universe?

programme.title: Paranormal State: Vendetta
programme.desc: P.R.S. investigates claims of supernatural revenge in the Pennsylvania Poconos. When a client's new boyfriend moves in, does the paranormal move in with him? Or did her ex put a hex on her house and the entire family?

programme.title: Paranormal State: Dwelling of the Dead
programme.desc: A single mom claims she is being physically assaulted by a spirit in her Kentucky home. Ryan first explores a natural explanation for the alleged phenomena. But the client's five-year-old son also sees spirits, and his sightings appear to line up.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Ladder
programme.desc: A large family in Shrewsbury, MA, has been living with a spirit for the last 40 years. To most of the siblings, the entity is menacing and evil, but Sandy seems to have a different connection.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Devil in Syracuse
programme.desc: The clients are new, but the spirit is all too familiar as Ryan Buell prepares himself to battle the taunting demon that has been following him.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Dead Legends
programme.desc: PRS and Psychic/Medium Chip Coffey investigate the famed Hotel Conneaut in northern Pennsylvania. Heavy doors opening on their own, sightings of a boy, a bride and a menacing butcher have the hotel's staff on edge.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Shadow Caster
programme.desc: PRS investigates an Alabama home where clients, Georgiana and her two daughters, are so terrified, they moved out after only 18 months. They have seen shadow figures, been touched and have a recorded EVP stating, "Look at me, get out of here."

programme.title: Paranormal State: Satan's Soldier
programme.desc: Mark and Kim can't sleep through the racket caused by unseen forces in their central Indiana home. When PRS and Psychic/Medium Michelle Belanger discover what appears to be blood in the basement, they investigate a history of violence in the home.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Woman in the Window
programme.desc: Ryan and his team lend paranormal assistance to a family who lives in a historic home that was once a part of the Underground Railroad. Does the answer to their haunting lie in the mysterious tunnels beneath the house?

programme.title: Paranormal State: Hide and Seek
programme.desc: Hillary and her nine-year-old son Hunter are being harassed by a shadow presence in their Victorian home in Newburgh, Indiana. Trap doors in the basement reveal artifacts from a bygone era, and the clients have recorded persistent strange noises.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Maesmawr Hall
programme.desc: Maesmawr Hall was initially a farmhouse, and was given to the Earl of Leicester as a hunting lodge by Elizabeth I. The ghostly figure of the Earl's white horse has been sighted in nearby fields.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Belsay Hall, Northumberland
programme.desc: The empty rooms of this abandoned 19th century country mansion are said to echo with the voices of phantom children when night falls. Will this children visit the team during their stay?

programme.title: Most Haunted: Gregynog Hall, Wales
programme.desc: Standing on an ancient settlement, Gregynog Hall was built entirely of concrete in 1840. Guests of the hall tell of a large man accompanied by a faithful dog that loiter by the main entrance.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Weald and Downland, Kent - Part One
programme.desc: The Weald and Downland Open Air Museum opened in 1967. With mysterious footsteps heard and furniture said to move of its own accord, the buildings are believed to be haunted.
programme.sub-title: Weald and Downland, Kent - Part One

programme.title: Most Haunted: Weald and Downland, Kent - Part Two
programme.desc: On their second night at the Weald and Downland Museum, the "Most Haunted" team tries to solve the mystery of the dark figure seen during their first night's investigation.
programme.sub-title: Weald and Downland, Kent - Part Two

programme.title: Most Haunted: The Royal Court Theatre, Bacup

programme.title: Most Haunted: Newton House - Part 1

programme.title: Most Haunted: The Galleries of Justice

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Thoroughbreds - Part 2

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Truly A Trophy

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Mission: Makeover

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Back in Business
programme.desc: Melissa is a busy mother of four who also runs her own online cosmetic business. But with not enough time in the day, she's stopped wearing the make up she sells and fears her aging looks will hurt her business.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: One Hot Pizza Guy To Go
programme.desc: Frank is a husband and father who has overcome hardships to start a small business of his own. But his decaying teeth give him an unwanted tough guy image because he never smiles. Frank's ready to shed the old image and start fresh.
programme.sub-title: One Hot Pizza Guy To Go

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Duty Calls
programme.desc: Kimberly met her husband in the Air Force. They lived an active lifestyle until his health forced him into a wheelchair. The stress of care giving and years of smoking has caught up to her and it's Kimberly's turn to receive some care.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Hair Today, Gone Tomorrow
programme.desc: Kim is a suburban wife and mother that never shook off the hippie-look of her youth. Now she longs for a more polished and sophisticated image than her long braid and wire-rimmed glasses.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Sue Chamberlain "One Year On"
programme.desc: Just a year ago, Sue Chamberlain was a 34 year old living in a 40 year old's body. Now, a year on, we retrace Sue's transformational journey – and pop in to pay Sue a return visit. Will she still be looking fabulous – or flabby?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Siobhan Wirdman
programme.desc: Step in Nicky Hambleton-Jones to rescue 37 year old Siobhan Wirdman and get this full time wife and mother to love herself and get her life back on track.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Facing the Music
programme.desc: KerriAnn is a Rock n' Roll singer who has recently lost her rhythm. Years of touring with a band and the recent loss of two family members has taken its toll on her looks. Our team of experts is going to try and make KerriAnn look 10 Years Younger.

programme.title: From Frump To Fairy Tale
programme.desc: Postal worker Kimberly is getting married and wants the look of a princess for her fairy tale wedding. She undergoes treatment for her damaged skin and then she's off with the glam squad to get the perfect bridal look.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Arresting A New Look
programme.desc: Mary is a busy police officer, patrolling the streets, chasing criminals and breaking down doors. Our team of experts is going to take Mary into custody and do their magic to make her look 10 Years Younger.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Liz Okoye
programme.desc: Clean living Liz Okoye from Bournemouth exercises regularly, rarely drinks and doesn't smoke. She thinks she's doing everything right in her quest to look younger: so why did one hundred people put her at 51, when she's only 44?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Back On Track
programme.desc: After going through a recent bout with cancer, Deborah is getting back on track with healthy living. Doctors help reduce her four eyes to two and smooth out a facial scar, and the glam squad performs their magic to help make her look 10 years younger.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Check My ID, Please!
programme.desc: Celina works in an unglamorous family business, manufacturing industrial degreasers; but dreams of being an actress, despite never auditioning. She turns to our experts for help with her appearance. Will she finally be ready to take center stage?

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 7

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 8

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1

programme.title: Wild At Heart
programme.desc: Danny is having second thoughts about the wisdom of uprooting his new family and ploughing all their money into a business venture that they know next to nothing about.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: Retirees Diane and husband Gary were just a few hours into their Pacific Island cruise of a lifetime when disaster struck. Diane toppled down a set of stairs and now she's in need of urgent medical attention.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: A leisure helicopter has gone down in Sydney's Royal National Park with a family of four on board, including three year-old Finn. The stakes are always high when children are involved. The rescue crew locates the crash site but can't get too close.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: Three surfing mates go missing in dangerous surf. The massive swell threatens to smash them onto the rocks in Sydney's Lurline Bay. The rescue crew is on a search and rescue mission but there's no sign of the surfer boys.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 6
programme.desc: Westpac chopper paramedic Bruce Kerr has a frantic battle to save a car crash victim with a life-threatening head injury.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 7
programme.desc: Auckland's Westpac helicopter crew races to save a 39 year old forestry worker who has been struck on the head leaving him paralyzed from the waist down.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 8

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 9

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 10
programme.desc: The Rescue 1 team are en route to the scene of a horrific accident. A pedestrian has been hit by a truck and is in a critical condition.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: A head-on car collision in Tasmania has left tourists Hong and Xeu Wu fighting for their lives. Ambulance crews have managed to stabilize Mr. Wu but Mrs. Wu is in a critical condition and calling out for her husband.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: A team of amateur scuba divers find themselves in deep trouble when their boat capsizes off Sydney's Botany Bay. The Westpac La Perouse crew spots the distressed divers while on a routine training mission.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: 65-year old Dave, a surf skier, is attacked and bitten by a Great White shark while training in the ocean. Dehydrated (after four days at sea), Margo needs urgent hospital care.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 5
programme.desc: When a massive earthquake strikes Nepal hundreds of traumatised and injured Aussie travellers need to be evacuated to Thailand. 19-year-old Alex from Sydney is in Phuket for a kickboxing holiday with his mates.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Honda / KTM / Suzuki

programme.desc: See and be seen. More than with other vehicles, this is vital with a motorbike. Lighting technology is particularly crucial to this. New technologies are gradually replacing the traditional incandescent lamps.

programme.title: Motorcycles: BMW Manufacture Berlin

programme.title: Motorcycles: Blacktrail E-Bike

programme.title: Motorcycles: Enduro Park Hechlingen

programme.title: Motorcycles: Triumph Thunderbird
programme.desc: A matte black chopper, the purist starter bike from Harley-Davidson. The Sportster 883 Iron is put to the test. Competition for the V2: a powerful 1.6 liter parallel twin, the Triumph Thunderbird.

programme.title: Motorcycles: BMW F 800 R
programme.desc: Today on motorcycles: We are testing the BMW F 800 R. A robust roadster with a lot of spirit, and even motorcycle world champions count on its agility.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Stereotypes on Two Wheels
programme.desc: It doesn't always have to be a Vespa. Three alternatives to the classic 125 scooter. City mobility in leaning angles without parking problems: with electro drive, with 500 cubic or with 3 wheels.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Triumph Speed Triple Carbon
programme.desc: Today on motorcycles: Carbon fiber on the Motorcycle - does that makes sense? We show what the formula 1-Carbon material is capable of.

programme.title: Motorcycles: KTM 990 Adventure
programme.desc: This time Motorcycles puts its eyes on Enduro bikes: the KTM 990 Adventure is Austria’s answer to the bestselling BMW R 1200 GS. Can the Austrian all-rounder for streets, gravel roads and long distance beat the dominating Bavarian bike?

programme.desc: Motorcycles presents the hottest bikes of Europe at the Custombike. The show in Bad Salzuflen is one of the leading fairs for exclusive motorcycles. This year more than 30.000 visitors from all over Europe have come to the event.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Harley Challenger
programme.desc: Motorcycles introduces you to the lightest power cruiser, the production bike with the biggest cubic capacity worldwide and a phenomenal all-rounder. Ralf Schütze reviews the Ducati Diavel with 162 hp and a weight of a bit more than 200 kg.

programme.title: Motorcycles: iMot Munich

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: After School Special
programme.desc: Tragedy strikes when a beloved teacher is poisoned in her classroom. As doctors fight to save Barbara Lewis’ life, Lt. Joe Kenda and his team delve into her personal affairs.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Eyes Wide Shut
programme.desc: A park ranger discovers the corpse of amateur boxer Corey Edge floating in a shallow creek. Kenda learns the victim had ties to the criminal underworld, and investigates a rogue’s gallery of hustlers.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: My First Case
programme.desc: In his first case with the homicide unit, rookie burglary detective Joe Kenda volunteers to work a bloody multi-victim shooting deemed “unsolvable” by the veterans.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Bump In the Night
programme.desc: When a pretty, young pilot is found in bed, bound and with a bullet in her head, Lt. Joe Kenda must determine if this was a random assault or payback for something that happened in the skies.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Death Rains Down
programme.desc: Restaurant worker Sharon Coleman is murdered in a hail of large caliber gunfire. Kenda must break through a web of lies to hunt down one of the most dangerous criminal masterminds he’s ever faced.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Teenage Savior
programme.desc: Over 2,000 people gathered at a local PETCO in hopes of a session with Cesar. This episode follows two of these troubled canines. Things get serious when Cesar's son joins in to help.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Buster, Jack & Marley and Sparky
programme.desc: Dog groomer Lauren asks Cesar for assistance with her three worst cases. Jennifer and Michael haven't been able to implement Cesar's techniques with one of their three dogs, head strong pit bull Sparky.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Widow’s Dogs, Drool Dog, Dexter Follow-up
programme.desc: A retriever mix, and wire hair fox terriers siblings, have turned into a combative pack. A Sharpei/Dobie mix drools excessively. Rottie mix Dexter travels to Los Angeles for a refresher course.
programme.sub-title: Widow’s Dogs, Drool Dog, Dexter Follow-up

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Optimus & Gigi and Sissy
programme.desc: Cesar lends his hand reforming Great Dane Optimus, who has a biting attitude, and Sissy, a fearful Shepherd mix rescued from a terrible hoarding situation.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Homewrecking Hounds
programme.desc: Cesar helps a newlywed couple whose dogs don't let them get close and another pair who met online and are nervous about introducing their dogs.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Buster, Holli, and Spike & Belle
programme.desc: Cesar cures Spike's depression with a new friend. An 8 year old blue heeler/Australian shepherd mix, is supposed to play the role of family alarm dog, but he does his job a little too well.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Willie, Make-A-Wish and Zena
programme.desc: A dog whose extreme fear of the stove has forced her owners to cook on a grill. Two dogs battle for control of the house. A Jack Russell terrier who can't handle the death of his pack leader.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: My Strange Addiction Special 2
programme.desc: In this one-hour special, we revisit six of our addicts whose stories shocked the world. Tune in for exclusive never before seen footage in this special episode.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Drinks Nail Polish & Ear Digger
programme.desc: Bertha has been drinking up to five bottles of nail polish every day for the past five years but her family is worried she's doing permanent damage to her health. Jamie can't stop digging in her ears.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Dating My Car/ Baby Powder Addict
programme.desc: Nathaniel has been in a relationship with his car for nearly five years, taking it out on dates, buying it gifts, and even getting intimate with it. Jaye has been addicted to snorting baby powder.
programme.sub-title: Dating My Car/ Baby Powder Addict

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Addicted to My Breasts/Tape Eater
programme.desc: Sheyla has spent $250,000 on 22 breast enlargement surgeries to achieve her 38KKK bust size, despite suffering a severe infection from her recent implants. Andrea is addicted to eating adhesive tape.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Eats Dirt/Extreme Toenails
programme.desc: Kristie has eaten dirt every day for the last 30 years, consuming more than five tons since her addiction began. Meanwhile, Ayanna is addicted to growing her toenails.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Addicted to Coffee Enemas/Licks Cats
programme.desc: Trina and her husband Mike have done nearly 7,000 coffee enemas over the last two and a half years. Lisa has been addicted to licking her cat and eating clumps of its hair for three years.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Extreme Hair/Addicted to Bee Stings
programme.desc: Asha hasn't cut her 21-foot long hair in nearly a quarter century and spends up to six hours a day grooming her ten-pound locks. Margaret has stung herself over 50,000 times with bees.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Addicted to Inflatables/Butt Injection Addict
programme.desc: Mark has been addicted to his 15 inflatable pool toys, eating with them, sleeping with them and even bathing them. Karmello has been getting black market butt injections for the last three years.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Identical Twin Obsession / Eats Mattresses
programme.desc: Twins Amy and Becky are addicted to being identical, looking alike, acting alike, and even weighing their meals to stay the same size. Jennifer is addicted to eating mattresses.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Addicted to a Doll/Eats Plastic Bags
programme.desc: Robert, a 23-year-old man who's addicted to eating plastic newspaper bags, an addition so intense, that he goes days without food. Catherine, a 48-year-old woman whose best friend is a doll.
programme.sub-title: Addicted to a Doll/Eats Plastic Bags

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Casting / Psychics
programme.desc: Profiled are Kevin, who constantly covers his body in plaster casts even though he is not injured, and Melissa who is incapable of making a decision without a consulting a psychic.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: My Crazy Obsession Pilot
programme.desc: My Collection Obsession takes you deep inside the world of four of the country’s most obsessed collectors each taking their material obsession to jaw-dropping extremes.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: 5,000 Kids_Tickled Pink
programme.desc: Pat and Joe are passionate about their extreme collection of over 5,000 infamous kid dolls. Kitty Kay Sera is completely obsessed with the color pink. She even wears pink clothes and eats pink food.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Million Dollar Manor
programme.desc: Born and raised in the bayou, Floyd and Robin Foti are living the American Dream. Their small business grew to become a massive food market. Now they’re looking for a million dollar home.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: All-Terrain Livin
programme.desc: Josh and Tiffany Chambless grew up living the bayou lifestyle and spending any spare moment exploring the swamps on their ATVs. Now, they’re looking for a place that’s baby friendly.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Wake Zone Getaway
programme.desc: Ross and Sarah want a new bayou home where they can walk out their front door onto their fishing boat. They discover a house on an island can make getting there tough.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Cajun Cabins
programme.desc: Pat and Joyce want their own slice of the southern frontier. They're looking for a hunting cabin that has the wilderness he wants, but the space she desires.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Redneck Riviera
programme.desc: Spear fisherman Clay and his girlfriend Jackie are looking for their first home together around Pensacola, Florida, an area where the bayou meets the beach, known as the Redneck Riviera.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Mississippi High Rises
programme.desc: Matthew and Lindsey are looking for a camp of their own. Lake Mary houses can flood, so the couple is looking for a high rise home, lifted 20 feet off the ground!

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Backwoods Paradise
programme.desc: Life in the bayou is all about family and passing down traditions. Blane is looking for a place where he can spend quality time with his teenage daughter, doing what their family does best – hunting.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Beached, Bayous, Backwoods
programme.desc: Jamie and his fiancée Brandi are looking for a home to start their life together near Gulf Shores, Alabama. But there’s one problem – Jamie wants a house on the bayou, but Brandi prefers the beach.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Mud Loving Camps
programme.desc: Trey and Jacob are two best friends who want to buy a backwoods getaway home for them and their families. They discover properties where the fields have been flooded to attract wild birds.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Burbs to the Bayou
programme.desc: Marty and Shelly grew up in the backwoods of the Mississippi bayou. But recently they’ve been stuck in the suburbs. So now they’re looking for a new home that will get them back into wilderness.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Biloxi Jackpot
programme.desc: Childhood sweethearts, Rowdy and Stevi, want to move into a starter home on the bayou. They love the excitement of nightlife and gambling so they’re looking for a house close to Biloxi’s casinos.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Cajun Inventor
programme.desc: High school sweethearts Donnie and Laurie have dreamed of having a weekend fishing camp on the bayou for as long as they can remember. Now, that dream can become a reality.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: City Girl and Bayou Boy
programme.desc: Newly engaged couple - Barrett and Haley - are looking for their first home on the bayou, but there’s one problem: he’s from the country and she’s from the city, so they’re sure to butt heads.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Off The Beaten Bayou
programme.desc: David and Blair love getting out on the waters of the Louisiana Bayou, so they want a weekend waterfront getaway home. But these houses come with their own hassles.
